		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="CN">
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="en">Life cycle assessment of mono-Si and multi-Si photovoltaic systems produced in China</descriptionOfRestrictions>
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="zh">对中国生产的单晶硅和多晶硅光伏系统进行生命周期评价</descriptionOfRestrictions>
			</locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">Reaction of reducing agents such as charcoal, coal or wood chips with silica sand in an electric arc furnace at 2000 ℃.</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">将炭、煤或木屑等还原剂在2000 ℃下与硅砂在电弧炉内反应</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The industrial process described is the production of industrial silicon using 97% purity level through carbon reduction methods. This high-grade silicon is specifically employed in the manufacturing of monocrystalline and multi-crystalline silicon photovoltaic systems. Such silicon is integral to the PV industry, where it is used to produce the semiconductor wafers that form the core of solar panels.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">所述工业过程是使用97%以上纯度通过碳还原法生产工业硅。这种高纯度硅专门用于制造单晶硅和多晶硅光伏系统。此类硅是光伏行业的核心，用于生产构成太阳能电池板核心的半导体晶片。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="fc799575-3db9-fc05-6872-cbf8d64577cd" uri="../sources/fc799575-3db9-fc05-6872-cbf8d64577cd.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">TrUzbcKQpoWKMrxNtlkcMCB0nPe.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
	</processInformation>
	<modellingAndValidation>
		<LCIMethodAndAllocation>
			<typeOfDataSet>Unit process, single operation</typeOfDataSet>
			<LCIMethodPrinciple>Attributional</LCIMethodPrinciple>
			<deviationsFromLCIMethodPrinciple xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromLCIMethodPrinciple>
			<deviationsFromLCIMethodPrinciple xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromLCIMethodPrinciple>
			<LCIMethodApproach>Allocation</LCIMethodApproach>
			<deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches xml:lang="en">The objective of this paper is to conduct a life cycle assessment of monocrystalline and multi-Si photovoltaic (PV) systems produced in China, and to analyze the methods of disposal and the environmental impacts of different methods of disposal.</deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches>
			<deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches xml:lang="zh">本文的研究目的是对中国生产的单晶硅和多晶硅光伏系统进行生命周期评价，分析废弃处理的方法和不同废弃处理方法对环境的影响</deviationsFromLCIMethodApproaches>
			<deviationsFromModellingConstants xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromModellingConstants>
			<deviationsFromModellingConstants xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromModellingConstants>
		</LCIMethodAndAllocation>
		<dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativeness>
			<deviationsFromCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromCutOffAndCompletenessPrinciples>
			<dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples xml:lang="en">Ban Hui and Ye Hongliang analyzed the data of five industrial silicon manufacturing plants in China. In this paper, we refer to their material inputs, selecting silica, charcoal, petroleum coke, graphite electrodes, water, and electricity, and calculate the process emissions according to the chemical equations.</dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples>
			<dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples xml:lang="zh">班辉和叶宏亮分析了国内 5 个工业硅制造厂的数据，本文参考其物质输入，选取硅石、木炭、石油焦、石墨电极、水和电能,根据化学方程式计算过程排放物</dataSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromSelectionAndCombinationPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples xml:lang="en">None</deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples>
			<deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples xml:lang="zh">无</deviationsFromTreatmentAndExtrapolationPrinciples>
			<referenceToDataSource type="source data set" refObjectId="43ac9052-e9ac-4b47-877f-783d34b7e56e" uri="../sources/43ac9052-e9ac-4b47-877f-783d34b7e56e.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">李鹞 &amp; 于随然. 中国光伏系统的生命周期评价. 环境工程 32, 119–124 (2014).  </common:shortDescription>
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="zh">李鹞 &amp; 于随然. 中国光伏系统的生命周期评价. 环境工程 32, 119–124 (2014).  </common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToDataSource>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="en">For life cycle assessment (LCA) practitioners, this data set can be applied to evaluate the environmental impact of the production stage of mono-Si and multi-Si photovoltaic systems in China. When using this data, consider the methodological boundaries such as system boundary, specific inputs like silica, charcoal, petroleum coke, and the choice of technological routes. Take into account the recycling and disposal processes of the silicon and photovoltaic systems, reflecting them correctly in the LCA model. The functional unit for this assessment is defined as 1 kWp of photovoltaic system capacity.</useAdviceForDataSet>
			<useAdviceForDataSet xml:lang="zh">对于生命周期评价（LCA）从业者，本数据集可用于评估中国单晶硅和多晶硅光伏系统生产阶段的环境影响。使用该数据时，应考虑方法论边界，如系统边界、硅石、木炭、石油焦等特定输入，以及技术路线的选择。还需要考虑硅和光伏系统的回收和处置过程，在LCA模型中正确反映这些过程。本评估的功能单位定义为光伏系统容量1千瓦峰值（kWp）。</useAdviceForDataSet>
		</dataSourcesTreatmentAndRepresentativeness>
